        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 4:10PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 410 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wilsonville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Talladega, Sylacauga, Childersburg, Wilsonville, Talladega Springs,
Vincent, Harpersville, Oak Grove, Bon Air, Fayetteville, Alpine Bay
Resort, Winterboro, Alpine, Logan Martin Dam, Logan Martin Lake, Lay
Lake, Country Club Estates, Beeswax Creek Park, Alabama 4H Center,
and Cedar Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
